I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense I have committed. I acknowledge my involvement in accepting a bribe, exchanging a sum of £4000, in order to prevent the publication of an article exposing a company's misleading environmental claims. I was aware that this company was falsely presenting its emissions data, as I had conducted the necessary research and discovered that they emitted one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than they claimed.

