Furthermore, I would like to bring to the court's attention that, prior to this offense, I had maintained a clean criminal record. I had only received one speeding ticket, which is a testament to my overall law-abiding character. 

In light of these circumstances, it is important to consider the mitigating factors surrounding my case. While I fully accept responsibility for my actions, the fact that I am pleading guilty demonstrates my remorse and willingness to face the consequences of my choices. 

I would also like to highlight my previous contributions to society and good character. Prior to this incident, I have actively sought to contribute positively to my community and uphold ethical standards. My commitment to living a life of integrity is evident not only in my clean record but also in my past actions and interactions.

Considering these factors, I urge the court to take into account the relatively minor impact of my actions, my clean record, and my demonstration of accountability by pleading guilty. I trust that the court will exercise its discretion with fairness and justice, taking into account the circumstances surrounding this case.

Thank you for your attention.

